  "text": "We estimated the population's average growth rate in the three habitats using the program ULM [CITATION_1] . The average growth rate and extinction probability in each habitat was estimated based on 1000 Monte Carlo simulations (50 yr per simulation) (Table 3) . Next, we used habitat maps of our area, field data for the density of this guild in each habitat type, field data for reproductive output per nest, and model output to estimate the following: (1) the proportion of the population in each habitat, (2) the proportion and (3) number of young produced in each habitat, and (4) the population growth rate across all habitats (Table  4) .",
